<Window x:Class="GremlinStudio.About"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        xmlns:materialDesign="http://materialdesigninxaml.net/winfx/xaml/themes"
        xmlns:local="clr-namespace:GremlinStudio"
        mc:Ignorable="d"
        Title="About Gremlin Studio v1.5" Height="420" Width="450" WindowStartupLocation="CenterOwner" ResizeMode="NoResize">
    <Grid>
        <Border>
            <materialDesign:Card Background="LimeGreen" Margin="10">
                <StackPanel>
                    <TextBlock HorizontalAlignment="Center">
                        <TextBlock Margin="12" Foreground="DarkGreen" FontSize="14" FontWeight="Bold" TextWrapping="WrapWithOverflow">
                            Designed expressly for developing Gremlin queries, with selectable raw json results and graphic vertices.  Click on any vertex for its properties, partition, and edges (if any)...double-click to create a new query tab for that vertex.  Click on an edge to set the query in the Clipboard.  Includes a lot of helper keys for writing perfect Gremlin syntax much faster.<LineBreak /><LineBreak />
                            Built on the great <Hyperlink Name="tinkerLink" RequestNavigate="hyperlink_RequestNavigate" NavigateUri="https://github.com/apache/tinkerpop">Tinkerpop/Apache project</Hyperlink>, 
                            especially <Hyperlink Name="florianLink" RequestNavigate="hyperlink_RequestNavigate" NavigateUri="https://github.com/apache/tinkerpop/tree/master/gremlin-dotnet">Hockmann's Gremlin.Net</Hyperlink>, 
                            as well as <Hyperlink Name="designLink" RequestNavigate="hyperlink_RequestNavigate" NavigateUri="https://github.com/MaterialDesignInXAML/MaterialDesignInXamlToolkit">MaterialDesignInXaml</Hyperlink>, the Tab Control from <Hyperlink Name="tabLink" RequestNavigate="hyperlink_RequestNavigate" NavigateUri="https://www.codeproject.com/articles/493538/add-remove-tabs-dynamically-in-wpf">Farid</Hyperlink>,
                            the toaster from <Hyperlink Name="designLink2" RequestNavigate="hyperlink_RequestNavigate" NavigateUri="https://github.com/Federerer/Notifications.Wpf/tree/master/Notifications.Wpf">Federer</Hyperlink>, 
                            and the permission from Francois Vanderseypen to freely use his clean approach in <Hyperlink Name="designLink32" RequestNavigate="hyperlink_RequestNavigate" NavigateUri="https://github.com/Orbifold/Graphite">Graphite</Hyperlink>.
                        </TextBlock>
                    </TextBlock>
                    <TextBlock HorizontalAlignment="Center" FontSize="14" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="DarkGreen">
                        (c) 2020, <Hyperlink Name="hyperlink" RequestNavigate="hyperlink_RequestNavigate" NavigateUri="https://www.yarondata.com">yarondata.com</Hyperlink>.
                        <LineBreak />
                    </TextBlock>
                    <Button Name="buttonOk" Click="buttonOk_Click" HorizontalAlignment="Center"  Background="Lime" Foreground="DarkGreen">Ok</Button>
                </StackPanel>
            </materialDesign:Card>
        </Border>
    </Grid>
</Window>
